node.text: Yesterday was #WorldOvershootDay - the day when we have used all the resources the earth can reasonably regenerate in a year. Artificially 3 weeks later than last year due to #COVID19. Noting also that this day would have come on 14th March for the US (and a similar date for other consumption led economies). A telling reminder that we are exploiting the world's resources unsustainably. It's no longer a theoretical date, the impacts on our lives through extreme weather and pollution are becoming ever clearer.

node.text:
I know a lot of people in Melbourne are struggling with this second lockdown. I thought sharing some resources that might help people to support their people may be helpful.

If you are not sure about asking someone R U OK or you are worried what the answer will be.

The @ruokday website has some really great resources to help prepare you:
To notice the signs that it might be a good time to ask R U OK?
To help prepare you to ask R U OK?

If you need help click find help on their website for an extensive list of support services available in Australia.

If someone’s life is at risk call 000
If you need immediate support please call
LIFELINE 13 11 14
BEYOND BLUE 1300 22 4636
Suicide Call Back Service 1300 659 467
Kids Helpline 1800 55 1800

You can also get access to 20 Medicare-subsidised psychology sessions up until 31 March 2021. It then goes back to 10.
The first step of this process is to make an appointment with your GP to develop a mental health treatment plan.

Look after yourself (in what ever way that looks like for you) Melbourne friends üíñ

#ruok #ruokday #mentalhealthsupport #mentalhealth #itsokaynottobeokay #covid19

node.text: Such a great job your doing Anna üôèüôèüôè
Such a great job your doing Anna üôèüôèüôè

Just a check in post for you all to let you know that we’re still continuing to send out our crisis food packs to those that are needing support across Bali. We had some information come through to us via a close Saudara friend; Putu, that a particular village near his home in the west was not doing well at all. The Balinese people are such a beautiful culture and have always had an amazing sense of community and sharing amongst them. They are incredibly selfless and will look at the wider village they live in rather than their immediate family to make sure everyone is ok. Everything is shared and they will look to make sure that everyone is ok. At the moment with money being incredible sparse and this meaning less and less available food, it’s harder for them to share. We delivered 30 food packs to this village and I’ll aim to share the stories of these people along the way so you can get a real insight as to why this food is vital and how your donations have made such a differenceüôè

This is Nurah Alit and he is 21 years old. He normally works peeling coconuts for a business that sells coconuts to many restaurants and beach clubs. As these are now all closed to to bo tourism, he lost his job. He has not worked for nearly 5 months, but it’s still expected that as a young man he will continue to provide for his family. The food packs you have donated are making a huge difference in the lives of these people. Anna xüíúüíú‚òÄÔ∏èüå¥

SWIPE to read the paper üëâüèº

Recent research suggesting gluthatione deficiency is a contributing factor to serious display of and consequences of COVID -19.
.
.
Initially, research thought it might be due to Vitamin D deficiency, and while that still may be true, it appears to be a secondary deficiency as a result of glutathione deficiency. (Last image) 
.
.
Glutathione is a major antioxidant and reduces oxidative stress and lowers inflammation. 
.
.
We need a strong, efficient LIVER - one that is not overloaded to make our own gluathione (“endogenous”) but we can also get glutathione from our diet (“exogenous”) in fresh fruit and vegetables.
.
.
Oh wait?! ü§öüèºü§öüèºü§öüèº
Did the simple fruit and veg just win the arguement again?! 
Hmmm ü§î must be a staple of a healthy person’s diet. 
.
.
I think you catch my drift ü§™

P.S. you’ll be able to find this paper either online or in @drkarafitzgerald ‘s bio x

node.text:
"SBS Bakal Tayangkan Program Musik ‘Inkigayo’ Lebih Awal"
.
‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ
.
Program musik SBS ‘Inkigayo’ akan menayangkan berbagai penampilan dari para idol lebih awal dari biasanya. Hal ini disampaikan oleh SBS secara resmi pada Minggu (23/08), dengan mengatakan, “Karena adanya laporan berita khusus tentang COVID-19, siaran ‘Inkigayo’ hari ini akan tayang lebih awal, pada pukul 15.05″
.
‘Inkigayo’ sendiri normalnya ditayangkan setiap hari Minggu pada pukul 15.50 KST, sehingga penayangan dimajukan 45 menit lebih awal. Episode ‘Inkigayo’ pada minggu ini akan menayangkan berbagai penampilan dari idol mulai dari ITZY, DreamCatcher, ONEUS, MCND, DONGKIZ dan masih banyak lainnya. Seperti yang diketahui, di Korea Selatan, khususnya Seoul saat ini dalam kondisi yang serius karena meningkatnya kasus COVID-19 yang bahkan dikabarkan telah menginfeksi beberapa publik figur
.
‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ‚ûñ
.

Meet our speaker 

@bensonuzoma 

In 2011, Benson obtained his Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS) degree from the University of Nigeria Teaching Hospital (UNTH) where he received an award for contributing positively to patient care and dedication to duty in the Neurosurgical ward as a house officer. 

He has a Master’s Degree in Business Administration with distinction from the Obafemi Awolowo University.

¬†

He worked with Jonex Specialist Hospital, Aba, as a medical officer. Thereafter in 2013, he served as the Chief Medical Director for the Oyo State National Youth Service Corps. He was employed as a Senior Medical Officer and Administrative Assistant at J-Rapha Hospital and Maternity, Ibadan, where he acquired numerous administrative skills with commendation for improving health services and carrying out his duties passionately.

¬†

Subsequently, he was employed by KBL Healthcare, a national Health Maintenance Organization (HMO) as the Medical Operations Officer covering South-West Nigeria. In less than 2years he was promoted to Head, Provider Administration, overseeing the company’s medical operations, risk management and client services nationwide. Later, he was hired by Oceanic Health Management Limited, one of the biggest national HMOs in Nigeria as a regional manager.

He is a medical professional with an entrepreneurial and¬† sales background.

Suicide Squad
Written & Directed by: James Gunn
.
James Gunn talking about his characters in Suicide Squad (üòÇ)
.
James Gunn's presence in both the Writer's and Director's chair is going to change the franchise a lot. The first Suicide Squad movie was met with a lot of negative critical review and after that with the failure of Justice League, WB and DC started making changes in the DCEU one by one from the bottom, and here today we get two new  trailers and a sneak peek of Suicide Squad, from the world of DC comics in a day, actually one 'new' because one is of course the 'Snyder Cut' other one being for the standalone movie 'The Batman'.
.
I'm so eager to see how the DCEU in going to change in the coming years!
.
Comment how excited you are!
.
Share your thoughts!
.

[COMING SOON PKD]

Assalamualaikum Wr.Wb
Pergerakan Mahasiswa Islam Indonesia adalah sebuah organisasi kemahasiswaan yang menjunjung tinggi nilai keislaman dan keindonesiaan. Nilai tersebut dijunjung secara bersamaan agar terbentuk kader yang memiliki pribadi yang taat kepada nilai islam dan cinta tanah air. Selain itu, sebagai bentuk tanggung jawab sebagai mahasiswa, kader PMII juga harus mengamalkan ilmu pengetahuannya, berbudi luhur, dan cakap agar dapat menjadi bibit unggul untuk melanjutkan cita-cita bangsa Indonesia.

node.text:
Although the #COVID19 global pandemic has drastically changed the way we operate, it has also offered us, at Sheron Ann Foundation, an unexpected opportunity to shift to a new way of connecting. It has widened our abilities to serve in ways we could not have imagined before.
Working at a distance has its difficulties, but through these struggles to stay safe and protect each other, we have gained a deeper understanding of the reach our advocacy has, and its ability to surpass any barrier it comes against. 
I want to give a special #ThankYou to our existing partners and our amazing Board Members for continuing to pull together and fight for survivors. 
•••
“You can do it on your own, but we envision a world where you don’t have to.” -SheronAnnFoundation
•••

node.text:
Hi, I’m Bree. üëãüèª
•
I’m a Boston girl who found my way by the Jersey shore üåä with my hubby and 3 year old boxer, Luna. üë©üèª‍ü§ù‍üë®üèΩüê∂
•
I grew up playing soccer, basketball, softball and even football all through high school! There was no better end to my day then leaving everything on the field/court. üèÉüèª‍‚ôÄÔ∏è
•
I got my PharmD from MCP in Boston, which required more time in üìö and less time in ‚öΩÔ∏èüèÄü•éüèà. This resulted in more than your typical “freshman 15”. üôÑ
•
About 1 year ago, I finally had enough and wanted my healthy lifestyle back! I joined @ww in July of 2019 and the #wwcommunity truly inspired me along the way. While working in the emergency roomüö® in the heat of #covid19 ü¶†may have paused my weight loss journey, I didn’t give up. WW is a lifestyle and journey, not a “diet” or destination. I hope we can help encourage each other through out our healthy journeys in this crazy world! üåé

node.text:
-
Kampung Warna-Warni Tigarihit di Parapat menjadi destinasi wisata baru bagi wisatawan yang menikmati keindahan alam dan keramahan masyarakat sekitar Danau Toba, Sumatera Utara. 
-

Peresmiannya yang dilakukan bertepatan dengan HUT ke-75 Kemerdekaan RI merupakan momentum membangkitkan pariwisata Danau Toba yang terdampak pandemi #COVID19.
-

Beberapa pemandangan menarik yang bisa dinikmati antara lain berupa spektrum tembok warna-warni, area mural yang instagramable, pertunjukan sunset di tepi Danau Toba yang eksotis, serta parade obor dan pertunjukan lampion.
-

Menparekraf Bapak Wishnutama menyambut baik peresmian Kampung Warna-Warni Tigarihit yang menjadi daya tarik baru di Danau Toba, yang merupakan satu dari lima destinasi super prioritas yang ditetapkan pemerintah. Kampung Warna-Warni Tigarihit menjadi wujud kreativitas dan inovasi dari masyarakat dalam memaksimalkan potensi parekraf serta upaya #BangkitUntukIndonesiaMaju.
-

Garut¬†-¬†

Warga Kabupaten Garut dihebohkan dengan aksi kawanan pemuda yang melucuti bendera Indonesia di pagi buta. Peristiwa tersebut kini tengah ramai diperbincangkan.

Kejadian itu berlangsung, Kamis (20/8) lalu sekira pukul 03.37 WIB di Kecamatan Wanaraja. Aksi para pemuda tersebut terekam kamera pengintai yang terpasang di lokasi.

Seperti dilihat¬†detikcom, dalam video rekaman CCTV berdurasi 23 detik yang beredar, terlihat empat orang pemuda berjalan di trotoar.

Entah apa alasannya, para pemuda terlihat melucuti bendera Indonesia yang ada di lokasi. Dalam video rekaman CCTV itu, terlihat para pemuda mencopot dua bendera merah putih yang terpasang di sana.

Dari rekaman CCTV itu juga diketahui, empat orang pemuda tersebut terlihat menggunakan sarung. Ada yang dipakai sesuai peruntukan, ada juga yang diselendangkan.

Ciri-ciri lainnya, tiga pemuda terlihat menggunakan kopiah. Sedangkan satu pemuda lain menggunakan fedora.

"Telah terjadi pencopotan bendera merah putih tanpa sebab di Jl. Wanaraja dekat studio Albara, Garut, sekitar pukul 03.37 WIB," tulis pemilik akun dalam unggahannya.

Kejadian itu berlangsung di Jalan Raya Wanaraja, Desa Wanaraja. Tepatnya di depan studio Albara.

Polisi yang mengetahui kejadian tersebut kemudian melakukan olah tempat kejadian perkara (TKP). Berdasarkan hasil olah TKP, polisi menyebut ada empat bendera Indonesia yang dilucuti para pemuda.

"Ada empat (bendera yang diambil)," ucap Kapolsek Wanaraja Kompol Liman Heryawan kepada wartawan, Sabtu (22/8).

Liman mengatakan, saat ini pihaknya tengah mendalami kasus tersebut. Sejumlah saksi dimintai keterangannya. Selain itu polisi juga memeriksa CCTV lain yang terpasang di sekitaran lokasi kejadian.

"Kita akan dalami orang-orang yang ada di CCTV," katanya.

Sementara itu, Kabid Humas Polda Jabar Kombes Pol Erdi Caniago meminta para pemuda untuk menyerahkan diri. Erdi meminta para pelaku untuk menjelaskan maksud perbuatan itu kepada polisi.

"Prinsipnya kita sangat menyayangkan perbuatan yang dilakukan. Dengan ada kejadian tersebut, kita mengimbau untuk (menjelaskan) perbuatan tersebut kepada kepolisian Polres Garut," ucap Erdi saat dikonfirmasi detikcom via telepon, Sabtu.

India is all set to get its first coronavirus vaccine. Covishield - the Oxford University- Astrazeneca vaccine candidate will be commercialised in 73 days, a top official at the Serum Institute of India said on Saturday.The phase III trials of the vaccine are being handled by the Serum Institute of India. The vaccine is likely to be the first one to move into production in India, sources had indicated to India Today TV earlier.A Bussiness Today report quoted a Serum Institute of India (SII) top official saying that the government has given the biotechnology company "a 'special manufacturing priority license' and fast tracked the trial protocol processes to get the trials completed in 58 days.""By this, the first dosing will take place today [Saturday] in the final phase [Phase II] and the second dosing will happen after 29 days.

Source:- india today

.

.
Oh ya, semua episode live IG creative talk bisa kalian lihat di IG TV, youtube dan juga spotify melalui podcast.

Beyond Mindfulness - Program Retreat Special  di Ubud, Bali. 

Selama pandemi ini kita mengalamai kondisi yang tidak menentu. Selama lebih dari 5 bulan terakhir ini kita dihadapkan pada kondisi yang membuat pikiran, mental, emosional kita bergejolak,  membuat kita was-was, khawatir, stress, bahkan ketakutan. 
Sekarang kondisi kita perlahan sudah mulai membaik dan semoga akan semakin membaik kedepannya. Kita sudah mulai bisa beraktifitas dengan tetap menjaga dan mengikuti protokol kesehatan. 
Dalam menghadapi kondisi seperti ini tubuh kita  membutuhkan  daya tahan tubuh yang kuat. Ketenangan pikiran, mental/emosional adalah cara alami untuk menjaga imunitas tubuh kita. 

Yoga, meditasi dan gaya hidup yang tepat dapat membantu kita meraih ketenangan dan harmoni pikiran, mental/emosional dan kesehatan tubuh kita. 

Anand Ashram Ubud sebagai pusat Pemberdayaan diri dan kesehatan holistik menawarkan program Beyond Mindfulness - Program Retreat Special  untuk Kesehatan Fisik, Keselarasan Mental/Emosional, dan Pemberdayaan Jiwa. 
Merasakan  pengalaman unik tinggal di Ashram: 
• Meditasi 2x sehari
• Agnihotra dan Yoga setiap pagi 
• Meditasi Mantra 3x sehari
• Kirtan/Bhajan 
• Satsang

3 Malam/4 hari (Tempat terbatas) 
- Termasuk makan
- Jumat (Check-in 14.00)- Senin (Check-out 11.00) 
- Biaya: 1.800.000/pax 

Diskon khusus bagi mereka yang pernah mengikuti program-program di Ashram/Centre kami di Sunter, Ciawi, Yogya, dan Bali - silakan check saat booking.

Informasi dan Reservasi Hubungi kami di  www.ubudashram.org  info@ubudashram.org 
Phone +62 822 3709 4865

node.text:
Wuhan, China once the global epicenter of the coronavirus hosted an EDM concert at an outdoor water park that saw thousands in attendance. Wuhan hasn't had a single case of COVID-19 since mid-May.

People in Wuhan, China are now enjoying packed pool parties after three months without new locally transmitted COVID-19 cases.

Videos of joyful-looking party goers at Wuhan Maya Beach Water Park taken on August 15 were widely circulated online this week. The photos showed a crowd of people standing in a large pool and sitting in tubes at an event that featured live performances.

With no masks or social distancing in sight, the photos of so many people together mark a stark contrast to images taken earlier this year in an empty Wuhan when residents were barred from leaving their homes. The city is considered ground zero for the new coronavirus.

According to the government-run Wuhan Daily, a manager at Wuhan Maya Beach Water Park said the park currently sees an average of 15,000 people on weekends. During early August, it saw about half the number of visitors compared to the same period in previous years. Still, the sight of massive crowds closely together has struck people in parts of the world where coronavirus is still spreading.¬†
